Title : Sophia Minnaert
Text : '''Sophia Minnaert''' is an American television journalist and the broadcast and digital features content director for the [[Milwaukee Brewers]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ballparkdigest.com/2018/06/15/personnel-news-milwaukee-green-bay/|title=Personnel News: Milwaukee, Green Bay|date=2018-06-15|work=Ballpark Digest|access-date=2018-09-30|language=en-US}}</ref>

== Fox Sports Wisconsin ==
In 2012, Minnaert was hired by [[Fox Sports Wisconsin]] (FSW) to work in their social media media department.<ref name=":0" /> Starting in 2013, she began as an on-air sideline reporter for FSW. During her time at the network, she worked both Brewers and [[Milwaukee Bucks]] telecasts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.creamcitycentral.com/the-4/the-voice-of-wisconsin-sports-sophia-minnaert/|title=The Voice of Wisconsin Sports: Sophia Minnaert|last=Stewart|first=Josh|date=2017-02-14|website=Cream City Central|language=en|access-date=2019-05-28}}</ref> However, following her hire by the Brewers in June of 2018, Minnaert's role with the Bucks ended.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/milwaukee/news/2018/06/13/milwaukee-brewers-hire-fox-sports-wisconsins.html|title=Milwaukee Brewers hire Fox Sports Wisconsin's Sophia Minnaert|last=|first=|date=|website=Milwaukee Business Journal|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

== Accolades ==
She won an [[Emmy]] in 2013 for the documentary ''Baseball in the Dominican Republic''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ballparkdigest.com/2018/06/15/personnel-news-milwaukee-green-bay/|title=Personnel News: Milwaukee, Green Bay|date=2018-06-15|work=Ballpark Digest|access-date=2018-09-30|language=en-US}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Minnaert is from Madison.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.madisoncatholicherald.org/news/around-diocese/5784-sophia-minnaert.html|title=Going pro: Former Catholic Herald intern is sideline face of Brewers, Bucks|website=www.madisoncatholicherald.org|access-date=2019-05-28}}</ref> In 2009, she graduated from [[Marquette University]], where she studied [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and journalism. Her mother is from [[Costa Rica]] and her father, Al Minnaert, is a well-known former Madison [[Edgewood High School of the Sacred Heart|Edgewood High School]] football coach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://stories.marquette.edu/marquette-alumnae-open-up-about-their-careers-as-women-in-sports-journalism-c6185c67290e|title=Marquette alumnae open up about their careers as women in sports journalism|last=University|first=Marquette|date=2018-12-04|website=We Are Marquette|access-date=2019-05-28}}</ref>

